latestPosts.caption:
Good things come in small packages.. 😍

#Ad @lakmeindia made a note of our universal love for minis and gave us these adorable Mini Xtraordin-Airy Lip Mousses!
Same amazing formula that you love as the regular size.. weightless, airy, matte, non drying, super pigmented - but in a smaller package!
Yes the formula is perfect but I also love these for so many more reasons - They’re great if you’re someone who likes to change up your look and try new things often so you don’t have to commit to a full sized product. They’re also so small that you can carry them around in your pocket or your tiniest purse! They’re more affordable too so you can save while your lips slay!

Cover up extreme dark circles in 3 steps!

Have got a lot of requests from people to show how to do this and it may seem intimidating at first but it’s surprisingly simple! Just remember that less is more because you can always build up the coverage but want to avoid cakiness. You can also add a setting spray on top for extra stay! 

Obviously I used a purple and brown liner to add dark circles so you can see how this technique works but trust me it’ll work the same if not better on actual dark circles. I’m using the @elfcosmetics colour correctors because I find them easiest to use and I like the creamy liquid formula!

Papaya milkshake for your hair? 😍

#Ad Step away from the blender unless you want a smoothie.. because this Moisture & More range from @milkshakehairindia already has papaya for volume and softness, milk proteins to strengthen, niacinamide as an antioxidant and hyaluronic acid for moisture. These actually plump your strands and I genuinely feel like my hair is thicker and shinier after using them. Milkshake is one of my all time favourite haircare brands and there’s not a single product of theirs I haven’t LOVED and this was no exception.. 

If you have dry frizzy ends that are in desperate need of some moisture and hydration these will become your absolute favourites!

Eyeshadow sticker??? 🤯 #notsponsored 

We’re definitely living in the future in terms of beauty! These are literally stick on eyeshadows from @hey_astrobabe - I bought these months ago but kept putting off using them because I didn’t want to waste them.. turns out you can even reuse them a couple times though so finally decided to give it a go!

Such a cool concept especially for festival makeup because let’s be real not many of us have makeup skills that can replicate these looks and definitely not in the 10 seconds it takes to apply these!

Oil free tinted sunscreen 😍 #Ad

I’m in the sun A LOT whether I’m on the beach, in the pool or wandering the streets of Goa - and this @clinique_in Superdefense City Block sunscreen SPF 50 has become a staple! 

It’s fragrance free, allergy tested and dermat tested, oil free so doesn’t feel heavy on your skin, 50 SPF - and the Stop Sign Technology helps protect your skin from UVA and UVB rays plus all the other pollutants and nasties in the air around you!

Sheglam top picks! #gifted

Apparently 3 products are sold every second from @sheglam_official worldwide and now it’s officially available from @tirabeauty - so here are my favourites out of the ones I tried! 

Color Bloom Liquid Blush in Love Cake
Eternal Beauty Liquid Eyeliner
For The Flush Lip & Cheek Tint in Cherry Picked
All In One Volume & Length Mascara
Jelly Wow Hydrating Lip Oil in Berry Involved

3 second sunscreen claim? 🤯 #Ad
Comment for the link! (This is a non affiliate link)

You guys already know I love @be.bodywise so when they asked me to test out their 3 second claim with their Ultra Light Sunscreen I was sooo up for the challenge! 

Short answer - it 100% lived up to the claim. 

Long answer - the formula is super light and airy and no matter how much I apply it doesn’t get heavy and even feels cooling on my skin! It’s also the only Indian suncreen tested for no hormone disrupters (I asked to see their certificates too) and it has a Korean anti acne technology so if you have oily or acne prone skin you don’t have to worry about about breakouts!

“This sunscreen STOPS tanning” 🤔🤔🤔

I’m sorry to break it to you guys but the only thing that stops tanning 100% is being indoors or covered head to toe in clothes. Yes sunscreens do protect from tanning more than if you weren’t wearing sunscreen at all and they definitely protect from sun damage and burning but if you spend several hours in the sun you will definitely tan to some extent no matter how much you reapply. There are tons of amazing Indian sunscreen brands that never make claims like this and only focus on the protection aspect - those are the good ones. 

Any brand that says their sunscreen will stop you from tanning isn’t being honest with you and is hoping you will also buy theirs in the endless hunt to find one that does that.

LED pimple patch?! 🤯 #notsponsored

I rarely break out so let me tell you I was EXCITED to get a pimple for the first time ever just so I could test this out. It’s the Riki Miracle from @rikilovesriki and it’s essentially a silicone light patch with a tiny battery that fights acne and acne scarring with concentrated light therapy! 

I was skeptical of it but somehow saw a tiny reduction in redness immediately after using it for just 6 minutes and after using it consistently for 2 days the pimple was gone with a small mark which also faded quicker than I expected! 

Love the little charging case it comes with and that it works quickly rather than regular pimple patches which sometimes need to be worn for 8-12 hours. Totally different effect since it’s not actually sucking out any fluids but I genuinely felt it made a difference and might even alternate between these and normal patches to get rid of a pimple FAST in an emergency!
